    <h3>Byte Hikers Overview</h3>
    <p>
    Byte Hikers is a comprehensive platform for users to explore, rate, and document their experiences on trails 
    tailored to hiking, biking, equestrian adventures, and more. With more than 60 million hikers and 9 million mountain 
    bikers hitting the 193,000 miles of trails in America's National Trail system annually, there is space for 
    technology to improve these experiences and encourage exploration. 
    <br><br>
    By implementing the database-driven website, Byte Hikers organizes and retrieves data after a user engages 
    in an activity on a trail. Details of user activities will be chronicled to provide useful feedback of personal 
    experiences such as duration of the hike, elevation gain, overall rating, and more.
    </p>

